text.section:
The Attorney General may deny, suspend, or revoke any license granted under KRS 367.97504 or levy civil penalties not to exceed five hundred dollars ($500), or both, or place the licensee on probation for up to twelve (12) months for any of the following causes:
Obtaining a license through false statement or misrepresentation;
Conducting or undertaking business in an unfair, false, misleading, or deceptive manner;
Entry of a final judgment or conviction for any crime involving moral turpitude; or
Violating any of the provisions of KRS 367.97501 to 367.97537 or any administrative regulation promulgated or order made pursuant to KRS 367.97501 to 367.97537.
